    "narrative": "For April 13th, the Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is anchored by **Corbin Carroll** (84.46), whose elite speed and prime positioning in the two-hole make him our daily ceiling play. The secondary tier of high-floor starts is dominated by our exposure to the Yusei Kikuchi matchup; **Jose Caballero** (71.90) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (67.92) both benefit significantly from the favorable opposing pitcher profile and the wind blowing out, with **Caballero** specifically seeing a massive 13% boost from his platoon advantage. Similarly, **Giancarlo Stanton** (65.85) remains a high-upside play in that same game, as the park factors and favorable wind help mitigate the risk inherent in his volatile profile.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involves the final spot, where **Tyler Soderstrom** (52.69) narrowly edged out **Max Muncy** (45.06) for the UTIL/OF slots. While **Muncy** benefits from a strong park factor against Nathan Eovaldi, the optimizer penalized him heavily for the 3.17 xERA of the opposing starter, which cratered his projection compared to **Soderstrom**, who maintains a stronger platoon advantage in this specific set-up. We are monitoring the status of **Dalton Rushing**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Josh Naylor**, **Alex Freeland**, **Jose Caballero**, **Trevor Story**, **Austin Riley**, **Corbin Carroll**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, **Seiya Suzuki**, **James Wood**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** closely, as the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters introduces a baseline risk; notably, the poor SP matchups for **Seiya Suzuki** (3.02 xERA) and **James Wood** (3.10 xERA) make them our most vulnerable starts, despite the high reward for **Wood** leading off. \n\nIt is worth noting that **Mickey Moniak**, **Brice Turang**, **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Carson Williams**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Kyle Karros**, and **Travis Bazzana** remain unavailable due to scheduled off-days or roster configuration, meaning our depth is effectively capped today. We are proceeding with the current construction to maximize SB opportunities, keeping a close eye on wind developments in the afternoon games that could further sway the efficiency scores of our fringe starters.",
